translated:
Lundquist, Ring, prakt, doctor, Gothenburg, b. 31/5/06 in Gothenburg to merchant Axel L. and Jenny Linder. Married on 31 with Eva Rodhe, a fil. lic. (philosophiae licentiate). Children: Cecilia b. 32, Christina 34, Elisabeth 36, Beatrice 43, Axel 46. — Passed exams in Gothenburg in 24, medical bachelor's degree in Uppsala in 30 and medical licentiate there in 35. Extraordinary assistant at Uppsala University Pathology Institute from 31-32, assistant doctor at the Surgical Clinic of the Academic Hospital in 32, at Sahlgrenska Hospital Medical Department and acting assistant doctor at Lillhagen Hospital from 36-37, resident doctor and acting assistant doctor at Sahlgrenska Hospital Medical Department from 38-41, assistant doctor at the Psychiatric Clinic in Lund from 42-44, practicing doctor in Gothenburg since 44. 

*Lundqvist, Sten Magnus Zachàu, civil engineer, Gothenburg, b. 4/7/96 in Uddevalla to director M. L. and Clara Zachau. Married in 20 to Elin Arnell. Child: Anita b. 26. — Passed student exams in 15, studied abroad in Oxford, studied at KSS, Thulins Flight School, CTH, received a diploma from the Technical University in Zurich. Traveled to England in 14, stayed in Switzerland from 19-24, USA in 24, Germany, Holland, Norway, Denmark, Italy, Poland, France and England on several occasions for various assignments. Employed by SKF in Gothenburg in 18, Götaverken from 24-33, ship inspector for several Swedish shipping companies, contracting for various domestic and international shipbuilding projects, mechanical expert in the Gothenburg district for the German Lloyd's classification society, lecturer in thermodynamics and oil engines at GTI since 31, self-employed consultant and engineering firm specializing in ships and machinery since 33, managing director and member of the board of A-B Marine Service. Member of the board for Rederi A-B C. A. Blidberg, magistrate inspector in Gothenburg. Member of The Royal Bachelor's Club and the Technical Society. Hobbies: car driving, sports flying.
